I'm also trying to determine why precisely `fsevents` and `node-gyp` are breaking for me with earlier LTS releases. If sdellis was encountering these or similar problems, then I can postpone looking for a solution for this.

princeton_ansible.title: [WIP] Updating the NodeJS release to 12.x versions

comments.body: Changing NodeJS 12.x releases to serve as the default may well trigger failures for application deployments which require lower releases.

NodeJS is a dependency for the following roles:

- roles/pulibrary.figgy
- roles/pulibrary.rails-app
- roles/pulibrary.dss
- roles/pulibrary.bibdata
- roles/pulibrary.pas
- roles/pulibrary.drupal
- roles/pulibrary.approvals
- roles/pulibrary.mudd

That `roles/pulibrary.rails-app` does explicitly use `pulibrary.nodejs` as a dependency (https://github.com/pulibrary/princeton_ansible/blob/master/roles/pulibrary.rails-app/meta/main.yml) ensures that NodeJS is installed for a number of roles throughout this repository. It may actually be more efficient to determine which roles are *not* affected by this upgrade.
